{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":33278,"duration_api_ms":32456,"num_turns":4,"result":"Before I show the refactored code, I want to flag something: the current design is **intentional**. The comments on lines 266-270 explain why:\n\n> \"one transaction per update batch to avoid a huge long transaction\"  \n> \"if one batch fails, only that batch rolls back and already committed batches stay committed\"\n\nThis is a resilience pattern — partial progress is preserved if a batch fails. Wrapping everything in a single transaction gives you all-or-nothing consistency, but you lose:\n\n1. **Partial progress** on failure — one bad row rolls back everything\n2. **Bounded lock duration** — a single large transaction holds row locks longer, increasing contention\n3. **The `failedBatches`/`partial_failure` tracking** becomes meaningless (any failure rolls back all)\n\nIf you still want single-transaction consistency, here's the refactored version:\n\n```java\n// Mark entities that need reprocessing to INIT in a single transaction, and return total updated rows.\n@Override\n@Transactional\npublic MarkForReprocessResult markAllForReprocess() {\n    int totalUpdated = 0;\n    String runResult = \"success\";\n    Timer.Sample runSample = Timer.start(meterRegistry);\n\n    try {\n        int effectiveBatchSize = Math.max(1, markInitBatchSize);\n        Pageable pageable = PageRequest.of(0, effectiveBatchSize);\n\n        long lastId = Long.MIN_VALUE;\n        while (true) {\n            List<Long> batchIds = entityRepository.findTopNIdsNeedMarkForReprocess(\n                    lastId, ReprocessState.INIT, pageable);\n            if (batchIds.isEmpty()) {\n                break;\n            }\n\n            Integer updated = entityRepository.markBatchForReprocess(batchIds, ReprocessState.INIT);\n            totalUpdated += updated == null ? 0 : updated;\n\n            lastId = batchIds.get(batchIds.size() - 1);\n\n            if (batchIds.size() < effectiveBatchSize) {\n                break;\n            }\n        }\n\n        return MarkForReprocessResult.builder()\n                .updatedCount(totalUpdated)\n                .failedBatches(0)\n                .failedCount(0)\n                .build();\n    } catch (Exception ex) {\n        runResult = \"failed\";\n        log.error(\"markAllForReprocess: failed, updatedCount={}\", totalUpdated, ex);\n        throw ex;\n    } finally {\n        markInitLastFailedBatches.set(0);\n        runSample.stop(markInitRunTimeCost(runResult));\n    }\n}\n```\n\nKey changes:\n- `@Transactional` on the method — single transaction, any exception rolls back everything\n- Removed `TransactionTemplate`, `failedBatches` tracking, and per-batch try/catch (no longer meaningful)\n- Batched reads are retained for cursor-based pagination (still efficient for large datasets)\n- `MarkForReprocessResult.failedBatches` is always 0 — failure throws, triggering full rollback\n\nThe batched **reads** (keyset pagination) still prevent loading all IDs into memory at once. Only the **transaction boundary** changed.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"408f93a1-205a-47f9-966a-d55475712213","total_cost_usd":0.182273,"usage":{"input_tokens":6,"cache_creation_input_tokens":16676,"cache_read_input_tokens":89536,"output_tokens":1330,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":16676,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-opus-4-6[1m]":{"inputTokens":6,"outputTokens":1330,"cacheReadInputTokens":89536,"cacheCreationInputTokens":16676,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.182273,"contextWindow":1000000,"maxOutputTokens":64000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"27f2084a-6ba0-4395-b391-e98a3161d7ea"}
